05/06/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- EU Regional Policy Commissioner Danuta Huebner kicked off a two-day visit to Zagreb on Monday (June 4th) to discuss preparations for opening talks between Croatia and the EU on the Regional Policy chapter of the acquis. 
Huebner met first with President Stipe Mesic, reiterating her support for Croatia's quick admission to the EU. 
She also expressed the European Commission's readiness to back authorities in launching strong and efficient management structures for pre-accession financial assistance. 
(HINA, EU website - 04/06/07)
